$ Oracle: Init parameter SHARED_POOL_RESERVED_SIZE
@ shared_pool_reserved_size

? `shared_pool_reserved_size` specifes the shared pool space which is reserved for large contiguous requests for shared pool memory.

? Along with the value of `_shared_pool_reserved_min_alloc` (obsoleted in 8i), this parameter can be used to avoid → development/databases/Oracle/errors/ORA-04031_unable-to-allocate_bytes-of-shared-memory as result of shared pool fragmation.

sa:

  → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/SGA/Shared-Pool

  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters, `→ development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters/shared/pool/size`
